HEADWORD: Debuscope
<hw>De"bu*scope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From the
inventor, <ets>Debus</ets>, a French optician +
<ets>-scope</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Opt.)</fld> <def>A modification of the
kaleidoscope; -- used to reflect images so as to form beautiful
designs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

